          <Base:Description type="brief">
             black steel and knotty walnut snaphaunce musket's long, sleek barrel
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="look">
             The long, sleek barrel on this musket is the cylindrical shaft connecting the firing mechanism to the muzzle through which a shot is propelled. A helix-shaped pattern of grooves and lands have been formed into the barrel of a firearm. It is the means by which a firearm imparts a spin to a projectile around its long axis, to gyroscopically stabilize it to improve accuracy and stability.
          </Base:Description>
